					<p><strong>The employer identification number (EIN)</strong> is one of=
 the most important nine-digit numbers assigned by the <a href=3D"https://w=
ww.irs.gov/">IRS</a> for new and existing businesses. This number is not on=
ly used for identifying the tax status of a business entity but also for fi=
ling tax returns, applying for business licenses, and several other busines=
s-related activities.</p>
<span id=3D"elementor-toc__heading-anchor-0" class=3D"elementor-menu-anchor=
 " style=3D"scroll-margin-top: 120px;"></span><h2>Key Points:</h2>
<ul>
<li>If the IRS considers you to be an employer, you=E2=80=99ll need an EIN.=
</li>
<li>Businesses may need a new EIN when the business changes hands or change=
s its structure.</li>
<li>IRS will only share an EIN over the phone with someone who is authorize=
d to receive it.</li>
</ul>
<p>Employer Identification Number, or EIN, is mandatory for businesses that=
 run under the jurisdiction of the United States. It is a unique nine-digit=
 identification number that=E2=80=99s assigned by the IRS. Employers rely h=
eavily on this number, which is formatted as XX-XXXXXXX, as a useful tool f=
or filing taxes. Sometimes, the terms <a href=3D"https://www.tax1099.com/fe=
atures/tin-lookup-tin-check-verification">=E2=80=9CTax Identification Numbe=
r=E2=80=9D</a> (TIN) and =E2=80=9CEIN=E2=80=9D are used interchangeably.</p=
>
<span id=3D"elementor-toc__heading-anchor-1" class=3D"elementor-menu-anchor=
 " style=3D"scroll-margin-top: 120px;"></span><h2>Who Needs an EIN?</h2>
<p>Businesses need an EIN if they tick mark any of the following conditions=
:</p>
<ul>
<li>Business having a minimum of one employee</li>
<li>File tax returns such as excise, employment, tobacco, alcohol or firear=
ms</li>
<li>Operate as a corporation or partnership</li>
<li>Withhold taxes on income except wages paid to a nonresident immigrant</=
li>
<li>Obtain a tax-deferred Keogh plan for employee pensions</li>
<li>Attached or involved in any of these organizations, including estates, =
real estate mortgage investment conduits, nonprofit organizations, trusts (=
other than certain revocable trusts, IRAs and for Exempt Organization Busin=
ess Income Tax Returns), plan administrators and farmers=E2=80=99 cooperati=
ves</li>
</ul>
<blockquote class=3D"wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout=
-flow text-center">
<h3>Stay Compliant with Real-Time EIN Verification For Your Business</h3>
<div class=3D"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-fl=
ex">
<div class=3D"wp-block-button">
<a class=3D"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button" href=3D"https://web.ta=
x1099.com/#/signup?ref=3Dblog">Start verifying EINs</a>
</div>
</div>
</blockquote>
<span id=3D"elementor-toc__heading-anchor-2" class=3D"elementor-menu-anchor=
 " style=3D"scroll-margin-top: 120px;"></span><h2>What is EIN Verification?=
</h2>
<p>When onboarding a new client or partner, businesses in various sectors a=
re required to follow KYB process. The legality of the company and its prop=
rietors are confirmed, and any possible hazards related to the partnership =
are evaluated. A valid EIN is necessary for a business operating in the Uni=
ted States to conduct certain financial and insurance-related operations as=
 well as for lawful operation. As a result, proving the identification of t=
he company requires first confirming the EIN.</p>
<span id=3D"elementor-toc__heading-anchor-3" class=3D"elementor-menu-anchor=
 " style=3D"scroll-margin-top: 120px;"></span><h2>Ways to Verify Employer I=
dentification Number for a Business</h2>
<p>Verifying an EIN is not a big deal if you know the right way. Let=E2=80=
=99s find out:</p>
<p><img fetchpriority=3D"high" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://www.tax109=
9.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Ways-to-Verify.png" alt=3D"Ways to Ve=
rify EIN" width=3D"791" height=3D"429"></p>
<h4>1. IRS Database</h4>
<p>It is one of the most trusted sources to verify an EIN. The Internal Rev=
enue Service (IRS) offers TIN Matching tool on IRS e-Services. However, you=
 are required to register first, and this would take some time. The service=
 is primarily available to certain authorized users only. If you don=E2=80=
=99t fall into one of the authorized categories, you might not be able to u=
se the service. While their interactive verification (verify up to 25 EINs)=
 is quick, bulk verification (for large numbers of EINs) can take days, dep=
ending on the IRS=E2=80=99s workload.</p>
<h4>2. EC=E2=80=99s EDGAR System</h4>
<p>Using the Securities and Exchange Commission=E2=80=99s EDGAR (Electronic=
 Data Gathering, Analysis, and Retrieval) system is an essential first step=
 in confirming an EIN number. Any company that trades its shares on a stock=
 market open to the public must register with the SEC, produce reports, and=
 have its data available through EDGAR.</p>
<h4>3. State Databases</h4>
<p>Apart from federal resources such as the IRS website, several state depa=
rtments of revenue have their own online platforms for conducting EIN numbe=
r searches. These websites typically feature a search tool where users can =
enter the company=E2=80=99s name or other relevant information to find its =
EIN. It=E2=80=99s important to recognize that while the IRS issues EINs, st=
ate revenue departments may also issue state-specific identification number=
s under certain circumstances.</p>
<h4>4. Tax1099 Platform</h4>
<p>For a super-quick real-time search experience, we recommend Tax1099=E2=
=80=99s real-time TIN match feature which allows you to search 100,000+ TIN=
s within a minute. All you need is the entity=E2=80=99s EIN and the legal n=
ame (as registered with the IRS) to conduct a quick EIN check. You don=E2=
=80=99t have to wait for hours or days to see the TIN match results. Being =
one of the most trusted eFiling platforms, Tax1099 streamlines the process =
of EIN verification. You can also do Bulk TIN Match by uploading the data i=
nto the system. Ensure 100% accuracy while filing tax forms, avoiding error=
s and IRS notices.</p>
<p>Need Assistance? Write to us at support@tax1099.com or ask our AI chatbo=
t.</p>
<p><span style=3D"font-family: inherit;">Validate EINs against IRS records =
before you file</span></p>
<blockquote class=3D"wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout=
-flow text-center">
<h3>EIN Errors Can Trigger Mismatches and Results in IRS Notices. Validate =
